<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-22T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-22T19:00:00-05:00" n="767" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.516/0–2349: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Clark</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                            Canton</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-22T20:00:00-04:00">July 22,
                                1949—8 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Telcan 487. Re last para Cantel 637, June 23, no record Chi Emb opening here
                        question settlement reverse-lend lease. Subject mentioned in general terms
                        only during course war accounts negotiations summer 1948.<note n="45" xml:id="d767fn45">For correspondence on this subject, see <ref target="frus1948v08#pg_686">
                                <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1948, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">viii</hi>, pp. 686</ref> ff.</note> Dept
                        unaware basis rumored Chi Govt claims since no reverse lend-lease
                        transactions reported by Chinese. Urinfo doubtful they wld be given
                        favorable consideration if presented. Any event Dept eld not consider
                        settlement reverse lend-lease separately from overall settlement war
                        accounts.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>